If $V=IR$ for a constant voltage $V$, then the total voltage of the circuit can be expressed as $V=(40)(3)=120$. Thus, when the resistance $R$ is $20$ ohms, the equation becomes: \begin{align*} 120& =(I)(20)
\\\Rightarrow\qquad I& =\frac{120}{20}
\\ I& =\boxed{6}
\end{align*}

